<subSubSection id="C3676536FF8DFF9FFF78EB1AFA6FE070" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="589" pageId="1" pageNumber="588" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF8DFF9FFF78EB1AFA6FE070" blockId="1.[151,1437,1735,2013]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1437,151,789]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="589" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8DFF9CFF78EB1AFEBFE6F8" bold="true" box="[199,321,1916,1941]" pageId="1" pageNumber="588">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body entirely black, with whitish setae. Clypeus rugulose, submarginally polished and impunctate, with four blunt teeth on anterior margin and median submarginal tubercle. Scape subcarinate beneath on distal onethird. Metasomal tergum 1 with two short longitudinal lateral carinae on each side. Metasomal sternum 6 with posterior margin deeply notched on each side and with prominent pair sublateral processes on each side. Hypopygium (sternum 8) strongly sculptured, with lateral peg-like process, and broadly and unevenly emarginate posteriorly; lateral process with four strong setae mixed with shorter ones; median emargination with a pair of strong setae on each side. Paramere with long dense thin setae, without few slightly stronger long setae near base.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3676536FF8EFF99FF78ED41FE60E5D5" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="591" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF8EFF9FFF78ED41FA96E0E5" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8EFF9FFF78ED41FEA7E02D" bold="true" box="[199,345,295,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="54C6881FFF8EFF9FFEDDED41FE30E02D" box="[354,462,295,320]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Holotype</typeStatus>
. Male (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFD98ED41FD95E02D" box="[551,619,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1613,1635]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,844,1588]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,844,1588]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype, habitus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.9 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803822/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity id="4C859B58FF8EFF9FFCA1ED41FC55E052" box="[798,939,295,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.7" metricValueMax="9.8" metricValueMin="7.6" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" unit="mm" value="8.7" valueMax="9.8" valueMin="7.6">7.6–9.8 mm</quantity>
. Forewing length 
<quantity id="4C859B58FF8EFF9FFBC1ED41FAF5E052" box="[1150,1291,295,320]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.95" metricValueMax="7.7" metricValueMin="6.2" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" unit="mm" value="6.95" valueMax="7.7" valueMin="6.2">6.2–7.7 mm</quantity>
. Body black except apicoventral spot on scape, fore spurs piceous, mid- and hind spurs whitish. Wing infuscate on distal half. Body and legs with whitish setae. Scape with longer, pedicel and flagellum with shorter whitish setae (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFAAAED09FAA5E0E5" box="[1301,1371,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF8EFF9FFF78EDF2FAD4E278" blockId="2.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8EFF9FFF78EDF2FEF5E0C0" box="[199,267,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Head.</emphasis>
Relative width of head and mesosoma including tegulae = 9.8:10.4. Head densely and coarsely punctate (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFF20EDD1FEF8E0BD" box="[159,262,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Figs 3–5</figureCitation>
). The ratio of postocellar (interocellar) distance: ocellocular distance: distance between inner edges of posterior ocellus and anterior ocellus: diameter of anterior ocellus (
<typeStatus id="54C6881FFF8EFF9FFBE4EDBAFB43E099" box="[1115,1213,476,500]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">paratype</typeStatus>
in brackets) = 23(15):75(42):18(11):21(14). Transverse with vertex slightly rounded, and without elevation behind posterior ocelli (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFF5AEE42FED5E351" box="[229,299,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Posterodorsal margin of head slightly curved in frontal view (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFC49EE42FBC5E351" box="[1014,1083,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
). Scape subcarinate beneath on distal one third. Relative proportion of length to width of antennal segment as follows: scape (108:21), pedicel (21:18), F1(20:18), F2(25:21), F3(26:23), F4(28:24), F5(28:24), F6(26:24), F7(24:23), F8(20:23), F9(19:22), F10(21:19), F11(42:17) (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFE0EEEE9FE09E3C5" box="[433,503,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Mandible tridentate, with subapical tooth smaller than other two (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFB4DEEE9FAC9E3C5" box="[1266,1335,655,680]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
); ventral basal lamella gradually narrowed apicad without any tooth or tubercle. Clypeus rugulose, submarginally polished and impunctate, with four blunt teeth on anterior margin and median submarginal tubercle. Genal carina absent. Postgena plain. Antennal scrobes above with transverse carina. Occipital carina well developed dorsally.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF026635FF8EFF9FFF28EA2BFB90E70E" box="[151,1134,1613,1635]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803822/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" targetBox="[151,1436,844,1588]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF8EFF9FFF28EA2BFB90E70E" blockId="2.[151,1134,1613,1635]" box="[151,1134,1613,1635]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8EFF9FFF28EA2BFEEDE70F" bold="true" box="[151,275,1613,1635]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D3EFF8EFF9FFEA6EA2BFE1FE70E" box="[281,481,1613,1635]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Pherotilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brothersi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8EFF9FFEA6EA2BFE1FE70E" box="[281,481,1613,1635]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Pherotilla brothersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23A57D4FF8EFF9FFE58EA28FDC6E70E" box="[487,568,1614,1635]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8EFF9FFE58EA28FDC6E70E" bold="true" box="[487,568,1614,1635]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, ♂, holotype, habitus, lateral view. Scale bar = 0.9 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF8EFF9FFF78EAF3FC0EE6A1" blockId="2.[151,1436,1683,1996]" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8EFF9FFF78EAF3FEB8E7C1" box="[199,326,1685,1708]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Pronotum, mesoscutum and mesoscutellum densely and coarsely punctate (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFB1EEAF5FB18E7C1" box="[1185,1254,1683,1708]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Tegula mostly smooth and shining, slightly recurved posteriorly (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFD6DEAD1FCE9E7BD" box="[722,791,1719,1744]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Mesonotum without anteromedian lines or longitudinal ridge. Notaulus short, incomplete anteriorly, one quarter of mesoscutum length, (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFBA4EABDFBA1E799" box="[1051,1119,1755,1780]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Parapsidal line incomplete anteriorly and posteriorly, shorter and shallower than notaulus (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFC28EA99FC1DE675" box="[919,995,1791,1816]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Mesoscutellum evenly convex, not projected posterad, with dense whitish setae along lateral margin (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFC13EB45FC08E651" box="[940,1014,1827,1852]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
). Mesopleuron mostly coarsely and densely punctate, with dense whitish setae (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFD1CEB21FD13E60D" box="[675,749,1863,1888]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Mesopleuron along promesopleural suture longitudinally striate, along mesometapleural suture smooth. Metapleuron and propodeum laterally smooth and shining (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFAF7EB0DFA70E6E9" box="[1352,1422,1899,1924]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Propodeum with whitish setae and reticulate rugose on dorsal and posterior surfaces (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFBDBEBE9FB54E6C5" box="[1124,1194,1935,1960]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,977,1000]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,265,956]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,265,956]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 12. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 9. Propodeum, dorsal view; 10 – 12. Metasoma: 10. Lateral view; 11. Dorsal view; 12. Ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm for 9, 0.7 mm for 10, 0.8 mm for 11 and 12." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803826/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
); with sparse whitish setae, and shining, transverse shallow depression on lateral surfaces (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8EFF9FFC22EBD5FC1FE6A1" box="[925,993,1971,1996]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="589">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF8FFF9EFF78ECFFFC80E1B9" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,289]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8FFF9EFF78ECFFFEFDE1DD" box="[199,259,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Legs.</emphasis>
Whitish setae denser on tibiae and tarsi than that on femora. Mid- and hind tibia without preapical dorsal or lateral spines. Fore, mid- and hind tibia with strong tibial spurs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF8FFF9EFF78EC87FAD1E071" blockId="3.[151,1436,151,289]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8FFF9EFF78EC87FEECE195" box="[199,274,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Wings.</emphasis>
Forewing with elongate sclerotized pterostigma; first and second submarginal and first medial cells closed, vein 
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8FFF9EFE9BED63FEBEE071" box="[292,320,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Rs</emphasis>
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8FFF9EFE80ED75FEB9E04C" bold="true" box="[319,327,275,289]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">2</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8FFF9EFEEAED62FE75E071" box="[341,395,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">3r-m</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8FFF9EFE7DED62FDF6E071" box="[450,520,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">2m-cu</emphasis>
nebulous; first submarginal cell 0.85 × as long as marginal cell (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8FFF9EFB62ED62FADFE071" box="[1245,1313,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 2 – 8" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1647,1670]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,340,1627]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 2 – 8. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF026635FF8FFF9EFF28EA09FC4AE7AE" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803824/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" targetBox="[151,1436,340,1627]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF8FFF9EFF28EA09FC4AE7AE" blockId="3.[151,1436,1647,1731]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8FFF9EFF28EA09FEC2E7E8" bold="true" box="[151,316,1647,1670]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">FIGURES 2–8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D3EFF8FFF9EFEFCEA16FDF3E7EB" box="[323,525,1648,1670]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Pherotilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brothersi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8FFF9EFEFCEA16FDF3E7EB" box="[323,525,1648,1670]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">
Pherotilla 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D3EFF8FFF9EFE0EEA16FDF3E7EB" box="[433,525,1648,1670]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" rank="species" species="brothersi" status="sp. nov.">brothersi</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23A57D4FF8FFF9EFDAAEA16FD99E7E8" box="[533,615,1648,1669]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8FFF9EFDAAEA16FD99E7E8" bold="true" box="[533,615,1648,1669]" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, ♂, holotype. 2. Antenna; 3. Head, frontal view; 4. Head, dorsal view; 5. Head and mesosoma, dorsal view; 6. Head and mesosoma, lateral view; 7. Fore wing; 8. Hind wing. Scale bars = 0.3 mm for 2, 0.4 mm for 3, 0.45 mm for 4, 0.7 mm for 5, 0.9 mm for 6 and 7, and 1.1 mm for 8.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF8FFF99FF78EA97FB39E1B8" blockId="3.[151,1437,1776,2017]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="591" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF8FFF9EFF78EA97FEBDE665" box="[199,323,1777,1800]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Metasoma.</emphasis>
Metasomal segment 1 densely and coarsely punctate, other segments moderately punctate, each segment fringed apically with longer and denser, whitish setae (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8FFF9EFCD6EB72FC13E640" box="[873,1005,1812,1837]" captionStart="FIGURES 9 – 12" captionStartId="4.[151,264,977,1000]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,265,956]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,265,956]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 9 – 12. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 9. Propodeum, dorsal view; 10 – 12. Metasoma: 10. Lateral view; 11. Dorsal view; 12. Ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm for 9, 0.7 mm for 10, 0.8 mm for 11 and 12." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803826/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Figs 10–12</figureCitation>
). Metasomal segment 1 three-quarters as long as hind femur; with two short basal longitudinal lateral carinae on each side of tergum 1; sternum roof like without carina. Metasomal sternum 6 with posterior margin deeply notched on each side and with prominent pair sublateral processes on each side. Pygidium (tergum 7) with median, subgibbose, smooth longitudinal area ending before apex on area length, with apical margin rounded, preapical area smooth, other part of tergum with small punctures mixed with twice larger but sparser ones (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF8FFF9EFD4EEBAEFCB8E68C" box="[753,838,1992,2017]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1514,1537]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,195,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,195,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 19. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 13. Metasomal tergum 7, dorsal view; 14 – 16. Hypopygium: 14. Ventral view, anterior to left; 15. Lateral view, anterior to left; 16. Posterior view; 17 – 19. Genitalia: 17. Dorsal view; 18. Lateral view; 19. Ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803828/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="590">Fig. 13</figureCitation>
). Hypopygium (sternum 8) strongly sculptured with lateral peg-like process and broadly and unevenly emarginate posteriorly; lateral process with four strong setae mixed with shorter ones; median emargination with pair strong setae on each side (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF88FF99FB87ECDAFB45E1B8" box="[1080,1211,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1514,1537]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,195,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,195,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 19. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 13. Metasomal tergum 7, dorsal view; 14 – 16. Hypopygium: 14. Ventral view, anterior to left; 15. Lateral view, anterior to left; 16. Posterior view; 17 – 19. Genitalia: 17. Dorsal view; 18. Lateral view; 19. Ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803828/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Figs 14–16</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF026635FF88FF99FF28EFB7FB79E56B" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803826/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" targetBox="[151,1436,265,956]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF88FF99FF28EFB7FB79E56B" blockId="4.[151,1436,977,1030]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF88FF99FF28EFB7FEB6E28A" bold="true" box="[151,328,977,1000]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">FIGURES 9–12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D3EFF88FF99FEF0EFB4FDE6E285" box="[335,536,978,1000]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Pherotilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brothersi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF88FF99FEF0EFB4FDE6E285" box="[335,536,978,1000]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Pherotilla brothersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A23A57D4FF88FF99FD9FEFB4FD8FE28A" box="[544,625,978,999]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF88FF99FD9FEFB4FD8FE28A" bold="true" box="[544,625,978,999]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, ♂, holotype. 9. Propodeum, dorsal view; 10–12. Metasoma: 10. Lateral view; 11. Dorsal view; 12. Ventral view. Scale bars = 0.5 mm for 9, 0.7 mm for 10, 0.8 mm for 11 and 12.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF88FF99FF78E855FC3AE5F9" blockId="4.[151,1436,1075,1460]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF88FF99FF78E855FEC6E521" box="[199,312,1075,1100]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Basal ring moderate. Paramere with narrow apex slightly upcurved; with long dense thin setae, without few slightly thicker long setae near base. Penis valves asymmetrical, right valve longer than left, without setae (
<figureCitation id="13462A38FF88FF99FF61E81DFE9FE5FE" box="[222,353,1147,1172]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 19" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1514,1537]" captionTargetBox="[163,1423,195,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,195,1493]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 19. Pherotilla brothersi sp. nov., ♂, holotype. 13. Metasomal tergum 7, dorsal view; 14 – 16. Hypopygium: 14. Ventral view, anterior to left; 15. Lateral view, anterior to left; 16. Posterior view; 17 – 19. Genitalia: 17. Dorsal view; 18. Lateral view; 19. Ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/803828/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Figs 17–19</figureCitation>
). Volsella somewhat swollen with microsetae dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF88FF99FF78E8F9FE60E5D5" blockId="4.[151,1436,1075,1460]" box="[199,414,1183,1208]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Female. Unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3676536FF88FF99FF78E8A5FDDFE5B6" box="[199,545,1219,1244]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF88FF99FF78E8A5FDDFE5B6" blockId="4.[151,1436,1075,1460]" box="[199,545,1219,1244]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF88FF99FF78E8A5FE9EE5B1" bold="true" box="[199,352,1219,1244]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F36A762DFF88FF99FED8E8A5FE54E5B1" box="[359,426,1219,1244]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49B9F85FFF88FF99FE06E8A5FDEBE5B6" box="[441,533,1219,1243]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3676536FF88FF99FF78E881FDE7E406" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF88FF99FF78E881FDE7E406" blockId="4.[151,1436,1075,1460]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF88FF99FF78E881FEC5E46D" bold="true" box="[199,315,1255,1280]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D3EFF88FF99FE72E88EFDB3E46D" box="[461,589,1255,1280]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Pherotilla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brothersi">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF88FF99FE72E88EFDB3E46D" box="[461,589,1255,1280]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. brothersi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to that of 
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF88FF99FC93E88EFC52E592" box="[812,940,1256,1279]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. oceanica</emphasis>
, but differs in having body entirely black (at least antenna, mandible, tegula and legs partly reddish-brown in 
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF88FF99FC36E96AFBF3E44E" box="[905,1037,1292,1315]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. oceanica</emphasis>
); paramere with dense long setae, without longer thicker setae along basodorsal margin (with dense short setae, and one longer thicker setae along basodorsal margin in 
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF88FF99FE37E932FDF7E406" box="[392,521,1364,1387]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">P. oceanica</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3676536FF88FF99FF78E911FD99E4D9" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BC236BDFF88FF99FF78E911FD99E4D9" blockId="4.[151,1436,1075,1460]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">
<emphasis id="B909EAAFFF88FF99FF78E911FEB0E4FD" bold="true" box="[199,334,1399,1424]" pageId="4" pageNumber="591">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species is dedicated to Denis J. Brothers, the world authority in 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D3EFF88FF99FB37E911FAFEE4FD" box="[1160,1280,1399,1424]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Mutillidae</taxonomicName>
, who recently revised the subfamily 
<taxonomicName id="4C7D4D3EFF88FF99FE30E9FDFD9DE4D9" box="[399,611,1435,1460]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="591" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Rhopalomutillinae">Rhopalomutillinae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
